        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "The deleted `force_capture_rustdoc_baseline_for_layer` entry is described with by-value `std::path::Path`/`str`/`TdddLayerBinding` parameters. That is not a valid Rust signature and is inconsistent with the borrowed signature style used for the related domain port, so the infrastructure catalogue is semantically wrong.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/ci-shorten-review-gate-fix-2026-06-01/infrastructure-types.json",
              "line": 11,
              "category": "factual error"
            },
            {
              "message": "`T005` and `T006` are marked `status: done` even though both have `commit_hash: null`, and the surrounding summary says they may be committed after `T003`. That makes the task ledger internally inconsistent about whether those tasks are actually complete.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/ci-shorten-review-gate-fix-2026-06-01/impl-plan.json",
              "line": 29,
              "category": "contradiction"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:3462a0f9b75b9a0c1480c00cff329db43b61d8415227eb5f4c7e6d2552bb203d",
          "at": "2026-06-01T13:17:18Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "zero_findings",
          "findings": [],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:704942469a14f807ef59afa639bd045d4e09284a66afc621558dfa71982c13c9",
          "at": "2026-06-01T13:23:20Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "ADR 1206 calls `catalogue-spec-signals` silently passing on a missing required catalogue a fail-open risk, but the decision then makes `type-signals` unconditionally skip missing catalogues as well and later claims that this structurally resolves the fail-open. If a missing required catalogue is a fail-open, the decision expands that behavior; if it is acceptable absent-input handling, the context/rationale is wrong. The ADR needs to reconcile that design intent before the downstream spec can be considered coherent.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "knowledge/adr/2026-06-01-1206-remove-lenient-and-force-flag-paths.md",
              "line": 27,
              "category": "contradiction"
            },
            {
              "message": "`CN-04` says `cargo make ci` must pass at each commit, and the new T005/T006 tasks are explicitly described as independently committable follow-up implementation tasks that also require `cargo make ci`. However `task-coverage.json` maps `CN-04` only to T004, which occurs before T005/T006 and cannot cover their commits. This makes the coverage artifact inconsistent with the plan's global CI-pass constraint for the newly added tasks.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/ci-shorten-review-gate-fix-2026-06-01/task-coverage.json",
              "line": 14,
              "category": "cross-doc inconsistency"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:704942469a14f807ef59afa639bd045d4e09284a66afc621558dfa71982c13c9",
          "at": "2026-06-01T13:28:19Z"
        },
